description: Officials in Kyiv did not overflow with condolences but used the death of Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny to push back on suggestions they negotiate with Russia.
title: Ukrainian officials say Navalny’s death proves Putin’s regime is ‘evil’

description: Hundreds were detained but mourners were not deterred from paying respects to Alexei Navalny, Russia’s foremost political opposition leader, who died suddenly in prison.
title: Hundreds risk arrest, and Kremlin’s wrath, to lay flowers for Navalny

description: The Republican front-runner has not commented on the dissident’s sudden death, even though he often riffs on what he would do as president when confronting Russia, Putin and the war in Ukraine.
title: Trump remains silent on Navalny’s death

description: In Munich, the specter of Trump and Trumpism loomed over panels about the war in Ukraine and dominated the behind-the-scenes chatter like never before.
title: Europe’s security elite braces for Trump, searches for back-up plans

description: Ukraine said it withdrew from Avdiivka as Russia claimed control of the city, in what would be a significant win for Moscow ahead of the war’s second anniversary.
title: What to know about Avdiivka as Russia claims control of strategic city

description: The government of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says it’s exploring other ways to allow aid into besieged Gaza.
title: Israel is trying to undo UNRWA, but few options remain for Gaza aid

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu dismissed as pointless further negotiations for a cease-fire to secure the release of hostages in Gaza.
title: Netanyahu calls Hamas demands ‘delusional’ amid impasse in hostage talks

description: Tehran is eager to disrupt U.S. and Israeli interests in the Middle East but wary of provoking a direct confrontation, officials in the region say.
title: Iran, wary of wider war, urges its proxies to avoid provoking U.S.

description: Advocates warn that time is running out for more than 100 hostages who have been held in Gaza for 19 weeks.
title: Growing protests call on Netanyahu to bring Hamas hostages home
